\noindent \textbf{Q1. [Physics - Newton's Laws \& Constrained Motion]} \\
A smooth wedge of mass $M$ is placed on a smooth horizontal floor. A small block of mass $m$ is placed on its inclined face, which makes an angle $\theta$ with the horizontal. An inextensible, massless string is attached to the block, passes over a frictionless, massless pulley fixed at the top of the wedge, and is finally tied to a fixed vertical wall as shown in the diagram. The string segment between the pulley and the wall is strictly horizontal. The system is released from rest. Let $a_w$ be the horizontal acceleration of the wedge (taking right as positive). Which of the following statements is/are CORRECT?

