\noindent \textbf{Q4. [Chemistry - Mole Concept \& Thermochemistry]} \\
A rigid, closed, thermally insulated two-bulb vessel is connected by a thin tube of negligible volume with a valve. Initially, the valve is closed. Bulb A (Volume = 2 L) contains 4 moles of $NH_3$ gas. Bulb B (Volume = 3 L) contains 6 moles of $HCl$ gas. Initial temperature is $300$ K. The valve is opened, gases mix and react completely to form solid $NH_4Cl_{(s)}$ (negligible volume). The reaction is exothermic, liberating $42$ kJ per mole of product formed. Assume $C_v$ for the unreacted gas is $21 \text{ J/(mol K)}$. Neglect heat capacity of solid and vessel. Find final pressure (in atm). (Take $R = 0.0821 \text{ L atm K}^{-1}\text{mol}^{-1}$ or $8.314 \text{ J K}^{-1}\text{mol}^{-1}$).

